name: Women's V-Neck Tee (and a Stew for you)
description:
Ladies, come and get it! Show the world what type of woman you are...a woman who loves her some good home cooking! A real woman eats stew is the motto for you, right? So wear it loud and proud. 100% cotton and with a splash of ink that spells out your culinary desires. 

PLUS! If you order within the next 5 minutes, you'll receive a "thank you tub" of stew of your choosing (when available). It's a you help me now and I stew you type of deal. I thank you in advance!

name: Men's Crew Tee (and a Stew for you)
description:
You want to impress your friends, but don't know what to wear? Well, here's your chance to show a little class. This snazzy piece of awesomeness is just what the doctor ordered. 100% cotton and a splash of ink that tells the world just what you like to eat...you can't go wrong. 

PLUS! If you order within the next 5 minutes, you'll receive a "thank you tub" of stew of your choosing (when available). 

It's a you help me and I stew you type of deal.

name: The Jambalaya
description:
With shrimp and sausage, this Jambalaya mimics those found on the Bayou. Tons of pep in its step and very filling. Need I say more? 

Main Ingredients:
Smoked Sausage
Shrimp
Green Peppers
Garlic
Tomatoes
Scallions
Spices, tons of them

name: Jerk Lamb Stew
description:
Straight out of the Caribbean, the jerk seasoning is a welcome reprieve from your regular routine. Best served over rice and peas for added delight. 

Main Ingredients:
Lamb
Onion
Carrots
Potato
Garlic
Chickpeas
Scotch Bonnet
Chilies

name: Tunisian Chickpeas
description:
This spicy treat gives credit to the harissa spice, which is a Tunisian hot chili sauce commonly eaten in North Africa. For those of you looking for a veggie option, this does the trick. 

Main Ingredients:
Chickpeas (of course)
Onion
Garlic
Harissa
Capers 
Garlic
